{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "cop2", "internal": "dof", "icon": "COP2/dof", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Depth of Field"], "extent": [59, 78]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Creates a depth-of-field mask, which describes how out of focus parts\nof the image are."], "extent": [78, 174]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operation creates a depth-of-field mask, which describes how out of\nfocus parts of the image are. Combined with a Blur or Defocus COP, with\nthe mask set to M and ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Per-Pixel Blur/Defocus"]}, " on, a depth-of-field\neffect can be done. This mask can also used as an input to color\ncorrection operations to accentuate an area of interest."], "extent": [174, 510]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["A point or depth plane (P or Pz) must be present in order for this\noperation to produce valid results."], "extent": [510, 614]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overloading VEX Parameters"], "extent": [16, 49], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator is implemented in VEX, which supports parameter\noverloading. If the first input has a plane which matches an\noperation parameter\u2019s channel name, the input plane will be used as\nthe parameter\u2019s value, effectively overriding it. The overloaded\nparameter is then evaluated from the plane on a per-pixel basis."], "extent": [49, 372]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "em", "text": ["eg."]}, " If the input COP has the following planes:"], "extent": [372, 422]}, {"lang": null, "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nC{r,g,b}\nA\nfogdens\n"], "extent": [422, 449]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["and it is fed into a VEX Fog COP, the fog density will be determined\nat each pixel by the fogdens plane, since the Fog Density\nparameter\u2019s channel name matches the 'fogdens' channel name."], "extent": [449, 638]}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [637, 649], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Focus Distance"], "extent": [649, 669], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The distance where everything is entirely in focus."], "extent": [669, 729]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Depth Adjustment"], "extent": [729, 751], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Increase or decrease the size of the area that will be out of\n        focus. Corresponds to the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["depth of focus"]}, " on a real camera\n        lens."], "extent": [751, 903]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Distance Adjustment"], "extent": [903, 928], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Adds a constant value to the distance (which is not the same as\n        adjusting the focus distance, which adjusts the dropoff as\n        well)."], "extent": [928, 1082]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Default Mask Value"], "extent": [1082, 1106], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The mask value to use when a depth-of-field value cannot be\n        computed (if the depth is zero)."], "extent": [1106, 1215]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "locals", "container": true, "type": "locals_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1215, 1223], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["L"], "extent": [15, 18], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Sequence length"], "extent": [18, 38]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["S"], "e